  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "title: \"DD-mec: Data-Driven Mechanistic Approach\"\n",
        "author: \"Giulio Franzese\"\n",
        "format:\n",
        "  html:\n",
        "    toc: true\n",
        "    code-fold: true\n",
        "    embed-resources: true\n",
        "jupyter: python3\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "## Overview\n",
        "\n",
        "DD-mec combines data-driven information-theoretic tools with mechanistic modeling to analyze biological systems. This lecture covers how mutual information estimation can be integrated with mechanistic (ODE/SDE-based) models to yield interpretable, causal descriptions of biological processes.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Theory\n",
        "\n",
        "### Motivation: Beyond Correlation\n",
        "\n",
        "Standard statistical associations (correlation, MI) do not distinguish direct from indirect effects, or correlation from causation. DD-mec addresses this by combining:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Data-driven MI estimation** (MINDE, TENDE) to identify informative relationships\n",
        "2. **Mechanistic constraints** (ODEs/SDEs) to prune spurious associations and identify causal structure\n",
        "\n",
        "### Mechanistic Models in Biology\n",
        "\n",
        "A general mechanistic model for a biological system with state $\\mathbf{x}(t) \\in \\mathbb{R}^d$:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\frac{d\\mathbf{x}}{dt} = f(\\mathbf{x}, \\boldsymbol{\\theta}, u(t)) + \\sigma \\boldsymbol{\\xi}(t)$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where:\n",
        "- $f$: known or partially known dynamics\n",
        "- $\\boldsymbol{\\theta}$: unknown parameters\n",
        "- $u(t)$: external inputs/perturbations\n",
        "- $\\boldsymbol{\\xi}(t)$: stochastic noise\n",
        "\n",
        "### Data-Driven Parameter Inference\n",
        "\n",
        "Given observations $\\{x(t_i)\\}_{i=1}^N$, we infer $\\boldsymbol{\\theta}$ via:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\hat{\\boldsymbol{\\theta}} = \\arg\\min_\\theta \\sum_i \\|x(t_i) - \\hat{x}_\\theta(t_i)\\|^2 + \\lambda R(\\theta)$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where $\\hat{x}_\\theta$ is the mechanistic model prediction and $R(\\theta)$ is a regularizer.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Information Flow in Mechanistic Models\n",
        "\n",
        "Once parameters are estimated, we can compute information-theoretic quantities analytically (for linear models) or via simulation (for nonlinear models):\n",
        "\n",
        "$$I(x_i(t); x_j(t+\\tau) \\mid x_{-j}(t)) \\approx \\text{TENDE}(\\hat{x})$$\n",
        "\n",
        "### DD-mec Pipeline\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Identify candidate interactions** using MINDE/TENDE on raw data\n",
        "2. **Fit mechanistic model** constrained by inferred network topology\n",
        "3. **Validate** by checking if the fitted model reproduces observed MI/TE patterns\n",
        "4. **Refine** by iterating between steps 1-3\n",
        "\n",
        "## Implementation\n"
      ],
      "id": "bc2d2453"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import torch\n",
        "import torch.nn as nn\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "from scipy.integrate import solve_ivp"
      ],
      "id": "0b2d926d",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### ODE Parameter Inference\n"
      ],
      "id": "c9d3b21f"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "def simulate_ode(theta, t_span, y0, t_eval):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Simulate a parameterized ODE system.\n",
        "\n",
        "    Args:\n",
        "        theta: parameter vector\n",
        "        t_span: (t_start, t_end)\n",
        "        y0: initial conditions\n",
        "        t_eval: time points to evaluate at\n",
        "\n",
        "    Returns:\n",
        "        solution array of shape (len(t_eval), len(y0))\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    def dynamics(t, y):\n",
        "        # TODO: implement the specific ODE system\n",
        "        # Example: simple gene regulatory network\n",
        "        dydt = np.zeros_like(y)\n",
        "        return dydt\n",
        "\n",
        "    sol = solve_ivp(dynamics, t_span, y0, t_eval=t_eval, method=\"RK45\")\n",
        "    return sol.y.T"
      ],
      "id": "2178dca4",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Neural ODE for Unknown Dynamics\n"
      ],
      "id": "0672117e"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "class NeuralODE(nn.Module):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Neural network parameterization of ODE dynamics.\n",
        "    Useful when the functional form of f(x) is unknown.\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "\n",
        "    def __init__(self, state_dim, hidden_dim=64):\n",
        "        super().__init__()\n",
        "        self.f = nn.Sequential(\n",
        "            nn.Linear(state_dim, hidden_dim), nn.Tanh(),\n",
        "            nn.Linear(hidden_dim, hidden_dim), nn.Tanh(),\n",
        "            nn.Linear(hidden_dim, state_dim),\n",
        "        )\n",
        "\n",
        "    def forward(self, t, x):\n",
        "        return self.f(x)"
      ],
      "id": "1751354c",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
